column69: Key Largo, unspecified location on Lobster Lane
column153: Python regius (ball python) first photographed crossing road on Snapper Lane 8/22/09, reported 9/21/09. Python was photographed and captured on Lobster Lane (next road to the south) on 8/23/09. Collected by MCSO Deputy Melissa Powers and transported to Everglades Outpost. Adult Python regius in photo appeared to be in very good condition, suggesting it was an escaped or released captive.
